## Standard Page Skeleton

```jsx
import { Helmet } from 'react-helmet-async'
import { useProducts } from '../hooks/useProducts'

export default function Shop() {
  const { products, loading } = useProducts({ sort: 'featured' })

  return (
    <>
      <Helmet>
        <title>Shop — Novaël</title>
        <meta name="description" content="..." />
      </Helmet>

      <div className="pt-[var(--nav-height)] container-nvl">
        {/* sections */}
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```

Top padding `pt-[var(--nav-height)]` accounts for the fixed `Navbar`. Content is constrained by `.container-nvl` (defined in `globals.css`, max 1440 px).

## SEO Rules

- Every public page: `<Helmet><title>{Page} — Novaël</title><meta name="description" content="..."/></Helmet>`.
- Title format: `Page Name — Novaël` (em dash, brand last).
- For dynamic pages (`ProductDetail`, `OrderConfirmation`): use the entity name in the title, the entity's `short_desc` (or `description`) in the meta.
- Don't add `<meta>` tags via plain `document.head` — always use Helmet so transitions don't desync.

## Data + Loading + Empty States

Every page that fetches must handle:
1. `loading` → `<Spinner />` or section skeletons (`<ProductCardSkeleton />`).
2. Error → toast.error(...) inside the hook or page; never silently swallow.
3. Empty → branded empty state, e.g. _"Your edit is empty"_ in CartDrawer. Don't render a blank page.

## Page Conventions

- Section padding: `py-20 md:py-28` for hero-adjacent, `py-16` for body sections.
- Section headings: small uppercase eyebrow (`text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-gold`) + display headline (`font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl uppercase tracking-[0.15em]`).
- Dark sections on `bg-black text-ivory`, light sections on `bg-ivory text-black`. Alternate them — never two dark sections in a row, never a section without a clear surface.
